# Analysis of the Main Target Image

## Count & Layers
The structure consists of 5 distinct blocks arranged in 5 layers from bottom to top:
1. Bottom layer: Red rectangular block with a semicircular tunnel/hole
2. Second layer: Green rectangular flat block
3. Middle layer: Yellow block with two half-cylinder shapes
4. Fourth layer: Green rectangular flat block (identical to the second layer)
5. Top layer: Red rectangular block with a semicircular tunnel/hole (similar to bottom but in opposite orientation)

## Spatial Relationships
- The blocks are stacked vertically, centered with each other
- The red blocks on top and bottom have semicircular cutouts facing outward
- The yellow middle block has two rounded half-cylinder bumps facing outward
- The green blocks serve as "spacers" between the other decorative blocks

# Required Blocks from Dictionary

Based on careful examination of the block dictionary, I need the following blocks to match the target structure:

1. Top layer: Block #1 (red block with semicircular cutout opening to the left)
2. Fourth layer: Block #8 (green rectangular flat block)
3. Middle layer: Block #13 (yellow block with two half-cylinder shapes)
4. Second layer: Block #8 (green rectangular flat block)
5. Bottom layer: Block #6 (red block with semicircular cutout opening to the right)

# Assembly Order

{
    Step1: Move block with index 6
    Step2: Move block with index 8
    Step3: Move block with index 13
    Step4: Move block with index 8
    Step5: Move block with index 1
}

This assembly builds the structure from bottom to top, first placing the bottom red block, then adding layers sequentially until completing with the top red block.
